{
    "info": {
        "_postman_id": "careerforge-api-v2-collection",
        "name": "CareerForge API v2",
        "description": "# CareerForge API v2\n\nOfficial API collection for the CareerForge Backend. This API provides comprehensive capabilities for CV management, AI-powered parsing, intelligent optimization, ATS analysis, and PDF generation.\n\n## Getting Started\n\n1. **Environment Setup**: The collection uses the `baseUrl` variable. Ensure it is set to your target environment (e.g., `https://propertied-geographically-scarlet.ngrok-free.dev`).\n2. **Authentication**: Most endpoints require a Bearer Token. \n    - Use the **Register** or **Login** request in the `Authentication` folder.\n    - The collection is scripted to automatically save the returned `token` and `userId` to the collection variables upon successful login/registration.\n    - Subsequent requests will automatically use these stored variables.\n3. **Workflows**: Common workflows include:\n    - **Upload & Parse**: Upload a CV -> Check Parsing Status.\n    - **Optimize**: Get CV Details -> Start Full Optimization -> Check Job Status.\n    - **Generate**: Select Template -> Generate PDF -> Download.\n\n## Support\nFor issues or questions, contact the backend team.",
        "schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json"
    },
    "item": [
        {
            "name": "1. Health & System",
            "description": "Endpoints for checking system status, health, and readiness. Useful for monitoring and Kubernetes probes.",
            "item": [
                {
                    "name": "Health Check",
                    "request": {
                        "method": "GET",
                        "header": [],
